

=Bio=

"Lean thinker and maker since 1974, son of an electrical engineer, global citizen, and at home in the social networks world. My education started after major in highschool in physics, maths, geography, and English with a bank apprecenticeship. From that on in late 80's I went into studying economics, and business administration focusing in production logistics, social media, project management and innovation. All these fields have stayed in my interest. I am passionate the see, and make the connections of the various dots, and communities. My common role is that of a "boundary spanner" across disciplines, and communities. 

"There is always a way to tackle a complex problem at hand, using the resources given."


